      "translate": "The Hunter's Table"
    },
    "subtitle": {
      "text": "The hunters ate first. Then they came back to teach the village how to follow them."
    },
    "description": [
      "◆━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━◆",
      "  CH.05 · THE HUNTER'S TABLE",
      "◆━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━◆",
      "",
      "▸ The Hunter's Table scroll describes a tradition.",
      "  After the hunt, nothing is wasted.",
      "  The carcass is processed completely.",
      "  The meal is shared completely.",
      "  The trophies are kept.",
      "  The knowledge is passed on.",
      "",
      "◈ BUTCHERING WITH FARMER'S DELIGHT",
      "  └ Cutting Board + Knife: break down raw animal",
      "    into component parts",
      "  └ Pig → pork chop + pork pieces + fat",
      "  └ Cow → steak + beef patty + leather scraps",
      "  └ Chicken → chicken pieces + feathers",
      "  └ More components = more recipes possible",
      "  └ Nothing wasted = more diet coverage",
      "",
      "◈ HUNTING CULTURE",
      "  └ Alex's Mobs adds 89 unique creatures",
      "  └ Many drop unique materials — leather variants,",
      "    special bones, rare drops",
      "  └ Ecologics adds 24+ animal variants with unique drops",
      "  └ Villager Recruits: Hunter unit type — assigns",
      "    auto-hunting to your village",
      "",
      "◈ SCROLL: The Hunter's Table",
      "  └ Found in: hunter's cabin chests, trophy rooms,",
      "    wilderness camps, ranger outpost loot",
      "  └ Research time: 20 min",
      "  └ Unlocks: full butchering system, hunting culture knowledge",
      "",
      "▸ The last entry in the scroll is a tally.",
      "  One mark per kill. Hundreds of marks.",
      "  The last mark is unfinished.",
      "",
      "▶ Find The Hunter's Table scroll [check]",
      "▶ Use Cutting Board to butcher an animal [check]",
      "▶ Collect 5 different mob trophy drops [check]",
      "",
      "◇ The Beasts scroll (this chapter, next chain)",
      "  covers Alex's Mobs specifically —",
      "  what each creature drops and where to find them."
    ],
